article.headline: Utah Valley St. 95, FIU 92
article.story: OREM, Utah -- Isiah Williams scored 26 points as Utah Valley fended off Florida International for a 95-92 victory Tuesday night. Holton Hunsaker added 25 and Jordan Swarbrick 23 for the Wolverines (6-7). Geddes Robinson had a double-double with 10 points and 11 rebounds. Alex Legion led the Panthers (5-7) with 22 points, including six 3-pointers. DeJuan Wright added 18, Phil Gary 17 and Eric Frederick and Cameron Bell 11 apiece. Utah Valley shot 53.4 percent (31 of 58) and 45.5 percent (10 of 22) on 3-pointers. FIU was not much worse at 49.2 and 43.3 percent, respectively. Williams' 3-pointer broke a 19-19 tie and gave the Wolverines the lead for good. The Panthers pulled within 81-78 with 5:15 left but no closer until Frederick's 3-pointer with 5 seconds left made it 95-92. FIU had one last chance when Jeremy Allen stole the ball at half-court. His shot nearly banked in.
